1165
01:19:35,500 --> 01:19:42,125
<i>♪ Where troubles melt like lemon drops ♪</i>

1166
01:19:43,375 --> 01:19:47,375
<i>♪ Away above the chimney tops ♪</i>

1167
01:19:48,208 --> 01:19:49,333
<i>♪ That's where ♪</i>

1168
01:19:50,583 --> 01:19:57,583
<i>♪ That's where you will find me ♪</i>

1169
01:20:00,833 --> 01:20:03,125
<i>♪ Somewhere ♪</i>

1170
01:20:03,208 --> 01:20:09,416
<i>♪ Over the rainbow ♪</i>

1171
01:20:09,500 --> 01:20:10,500
[song ends]

1172
01:20:14,625 --> 01:20:16,458
[Irv] <i>How would you describe</i>

1173
01:20:16,541 --> 01:20:18,261
<i>the young lady
who's about to come out here?</i>

1174
01:20:18,333 --> 01:20:20,166
<i>Well, I would say she's magical.</i>

1175
01:20:21,416 --> 01:20:22,625
[Irv] <i>I... I agree.</i>

1176
01:20:23,208 --> 01:20:27,250
[woman] <i>Thank you.
And I think she's strong and confident.</i>

1177
01:20:27,333 --> 01:20:28,791
[Irv] <i>Her name is certainly fitting.</i>

1178
01:20:28,875 --> 01:20:31,416
<i>It's true. She has a beautiful complexion.</i>

1179
01:20:40,666 --> 01:20:41,791
You ready?

1180
01:20:41,875 --> 01:20:42,958
Of course I am.

1181
01:20:43,500 --> 01:20:45,291
You're confident. That's good.

1182
01:20:46,125 --> 01:20:47,166
[Mother exhales]

1183
01:20:51,583 --> 01:20:53,541
Your father would be so proud.

1184
01:20:55,750 --> 01:20:56,750
I know, Ma.

1185
01:20:57,500 --> 01:20:58,500
[Mother sighs]

1186
01:21:00,666 --> 01:21:03,041
Jas, can you put that thing away?

1187
01:21:03,125 --> 01:21:05,166
This is a big deal.
I wanna capture the moment.

1188
01:21:05,250 --> 01:21:06,750
It's gonna be on TV.

1189
01:21:07,250 --> 01:21:08,250
Not this part.

1190
01:21:08,291 --> 01:21:09,625
[music plays in the distance]

1191
01:21:09,708 --> 01:21:12,000
What... what is that? [scoffs]

1192
01:21:12,083 --> 01:21:13,208
They're practicing.

1193
01:21:13,291 --> 01:21:15,791
Wha... You hear how slow they playing?

1194
01:21:15,875 --> 01:21:18,166
If they play like that,
you'll put everybody to sleep.

1195
01:21:18,250 --> 01:21:19,958
I'mma go tell them to speed it up.

1196
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:23,708
Ma, they the house band.
I think they know what they doing.

1197
01:21:23,791 --> 01:21:25,958
They're used to playing
for little white girls.

1198
01:21:26,041 --> 01:21:27,291
You from the church.

1199
01:21:27,375 --> 01:21:28,500
I'll be right back.

1200
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:30,083
[Jasmine whistles]

1201
01:21:30,791 --> 01:21:31,791
[door opens]

1202
01:21:31,833 --> 01:21:35,875
["Over the Rainbow" playing slowly]

1203
01:21:35,958 --> 01:21:37,083
[door closes]

1204
01:21:41,666 --> 01:21:43,041
Your mama still crazy.

1205
01:21:44,458 --> 01:21:46,750
But if it wasn't for her,
I wouldn't be here.

1206
01:21:54,083 --> 01:21:55,333
[Jasmine sighs]

1207
01:21:58,041 --> 01:21:59,208
Mmm, you look good.

1208
01:22:08,833 --> 01:22:11,125
[indistinct chattering in the distance]

1209
01:22:11,208 --> 01:22:12,291
[knocks on door]

1210
01:22:12,375 --> 01:22:13,375
Just a minute.

1211
01:22:14,416 --> 01:22:16,375
[neighbor] Listen,
I ain't got all day now.

1212
01:22:16,875 --> 01:22:18,666
Yo, who the fuck is that?

1213
01:22:18,750 --> 01:22:22,750
It's the boy from the other apartment,
the one complaining about the music.

1214
01:22:22,833 --> 01:22:24,000
Why is he here?

1215
01:22:24,083 --> 01:22:25,291
[Beauty] I invited him.

1216
01:22:29,250 --> 01:22:30,333
[neighbor] What's up?

1217
01:22:31,083 --> 01:22:32,125
[Beauty] Come on in.

1218
01:22:33,125 --> 01:22:35,708
[woman and Irv
talking indistinctly in the distance]

1219
01:22:35,791 --> 01:22:36,916
[audience laughing]

1220
01:22:45,958 --> 01:22:46,958
For me?

1221
01:22:47,541 --> 01:22:48,958
Well, they ain't for me.

1222
01:22:53,916 --> 01:22:55,541
Hey, I'm Sammy.

1223
01:22:56,833 --> 01:22:58,125
[sighs] I'm Jas.

1224
01:23:03,250 --> 01:23:04,791
[Sammy] So you big-time, huh?

1225
01:23:05,291 --> 01:23:06,875
Not yet, but I will be.

1226
01:23:08,291 --> 01:23:09,750
Yeah? What makes you so sure?

1227
01:23:10,458 --> 01:23:11,500
I have a gift.

1228
01:23:13,666 --> 01:23:14,666
Is that right?

1229
01:23:16,958 --> 01:23:17,958
[Beauty] Jas,

1230
01:23:19,208 --> 01:23:20,750
tell this boy

1231
01:23:20,833 --> 01:23:23,458
that no one can sing better than me.

1232
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:26,708
Can't nobody sing better than her.

1233
01:23:29,333 --> 01:23:31,958
Well, we just gonna have to see
about that, ain't we?

1234
01:23:38,500 --> 01:23:39,500
[chuckles]

1235
01:23:40,291 --> 01:23:45,333
Well, um, I just wanted to come back here,
uh, wish you good luck, give you those.

1236
01:23:45,416 --> 01:23:46,625
See you after the show.

1237
01:24:08,250 --> 01:24:10,916
- [Irv talking indistinctly]
- [woman laughs]

1238
01:24:11,000 --> 01:24:12,333
[audience laughing]

1239
01:24:19,791 --> 01:24:20,833
Why is he here?

1240
01:24:22,583 --> 01:24:25,041
- Relax.
- No. Don't tell me to relax.

1241
01:24:27,791 --> 01:24:30,000
I just wanted him
to come and hear me sing.

1242
01:24:31,541 --> 01:24:32,541
Why?

1243
01:24:33,666 --> 01:24:37,375
'Cause I told him I was a good singer,
and he didn't believe me.

1244
01:24:44,583 --> 01:24:46,625
Is that the only reason you invited him?

1245
01:24:48,750 --> 01:24:49,750
Yes.

1246
01:24:55,333 --> 01:24:56,750
When this is all over...

1247
01:24:59,625 --> 01:25:02,541
the only person
I wanna hear applauding is you.

1248
01:25:07,708 --> 01:25:10,750
I would applaud for you
even if you fall flat on your face.

1249
01:25:11,333 --> 01:25:12,333
I know.

1250
01:25:17,541 --> 01:25:18,583
[knocks on door]

1251
01:25:21,041 --> 01:25:22,041
Who is it?

1252
01:25:23,208 --> 01:25:24,291
[man] It's time.

1253
01:25:41,250 --> 01:25:42,416
[door opens]

1254
01:25:47,750 --> 01:25:48,875
[door closes]

1255
01:25:55,416 --> 01:25:57,416
[somber music playing]

1256
01:25:59,583 --> 01:26:03,791
...and she has this aura about her
that's magnetic.

1257
01:26:03,875 --> 01:26:08,583
[Irv] <i>Yes. I was drawn to her right away
when I saw her perform the other night.</i>

1258
01:26:08,666 --> 01:26:11,458
[woman]<i> Mm-hmm. I don't think
I've ever met someone quite like her.</i>

1259
01:26:11,541 --> 01:26:12,541
She's

1260
01:26:13,125 --> 01:26:16,875
<i>that kind of girl
that only comes along once in a lifetime.</i>

1261
01:26:16,958 --> 01:26:19,041
<i>It's... If I can say,</i>

1262
01:26:19,125 --> 01:26:22,541
<i>it's like God was showing off a little bit
when He made her.</i>

1263
01:26:22,625 --> 01:26:26,125
<i>- </i>[Irv] <i>Sure.
- That He breathed it on her vocal cords...</i>

1264
01:26:29,833 --> 01:26:32,708
<i>smiled when He made her spirit</i>

1265
01:26:32,791 --> 01:26:35,500
<i>and laughed when He finished that face.</i>

1266
01:26:35,583 --> 01:26:36,791
